  "title": {
    "rendered": "Debt Collection Attorneys:  Fresno &#038; Fresno County"
  },
  "content": {
    "rendered": "<div class=\"wpb-content-wrapper\"><p>[vc_row triangle_shape=&#8221;no&#8221;][vc_column][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<div id=\"pl-3664\" class=\"panel-layout\">\n<div id=\"pg-3664-0\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;,&quot;cell_alignment&quot;:&quot;flex-start&quot;}\" data-ratio=\"1\" data-ratio-direction=\"right\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3664-0-0\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"1\">\n<p id=\"panel-3664-0-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-headline panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"0\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\"><span style=\"font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; letter-spacing: inherit;\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-3185 alignleft\" src=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/iStock-910060330_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"463\" height=\"309\" srcset=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/iStock-910060330_2.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/iStock-910060330_2-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/iStock-910060330_2-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/iStock-910060330_2-272x182.jpg 272w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 463px) 100vw, 463px\" \/>The collection of a debt owed is a fundamental phase in any financial agreement, and failure to do so can have long-term fiscal implications. At the <\/span><a style=\"font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; letter-spacing: inherit;\" href=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/about-us\/\">Chuckstern Murphy Law Firm<\/a><span style=\"font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; letter-spacing: inherit;\">, we want to make sure your debt cases are handled quickly and efficiently.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"pg-3664-1\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;,&quot;cell_alignment&quot;:&quot;flex-start&quot;}\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3664-1-0\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"0.5\">\n<div id=\"panel-3664-1-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-editor panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"1\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\">\n<div class=\"so-widget-sow-editor so-widget-sow-editor-base\">\n<div class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">\n<p>Whether you\u2019re an independent contractor seeking money owed or a multi-national organization attempting to collect an outstanding debt, we can help you collect the money owed to you.<\/p>\n<p>Our debt collection attorneys in  Fresno and Fresnno County are ready to help you reach the desired outcome \u2013 and through the most direct and cost-efficient means. We service clients in and around  Fresno, Fresno, Thousand Oaks, Camarillo, Burbank, and Newbury Park.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"pgc-3664-1-1\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"0.5\">\n<div data-index=\"2\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\"><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div data-index=\"2\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\"><\/div>\n<div data-index=\"2\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\"><\/div>\n<div id=\"pl-3664\" class=\"panel-layout\">\n<div id=\"pg-3664-1\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;,&quot;cell_alignment&quot;:&quot;flex-start&quot;}\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3664-1-1\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"0.5\">\n<div data-index=\"2\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\"><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height=&#8221;80&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<div id=\"pl-3664\" class=\"panel-layout\">\n<div id=\"pg-3664-0\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;,&quot;cell_alignment&quot;:&quot;flex-start&quot;}\" data-ratio=\"1\" data-ratio-direction=\"right\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3664-0-0\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"1\"><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"pl-3664\" class=\"panel-layout\">\n<div id=\"pg-3664-1\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;,&quot;cell_alignment&quot;:&quot;flex-start&quot;}\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3664-1-1\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"0.5\">\n<h2 id=\"panel-3664-1-1-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_media_image panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"2\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\">Debt Collection Agencies vs Debt Collection Attorneys<\/h2>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"pg-3664-2\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;,&quot;cell_alignment&quot;:&quot;flex-start&quot;}\" data-ratio=\"1\" data-ratio-direction=\"right\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3664-2-0\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"1\">\n<div id=\"panel-3664-2-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-editor panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"3\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_image_attachment&quot;:false,&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\">\n<div class=\"so-widget-sow-editor so-widget-sow-editor-base\">\n<div class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">\n<p>If you\u2019re currently trying to collect on a debt, it\u2019s likely that you\u2019ve also considered working with a debt collection agency. While both collection agencies and law firms can help you collect unpaid debts, there are significant differences between the two \u2013 many of which can directly impact your odds of success.<\/p>\n<p>To collect unpaid debt, a debt collection agency will typically engage in a series of phone calls and letters to pressure the individual or business into meeting their financial obligation.<\/p>\n<p>However, if debts continue to go unpaid, the agency must eventually resort to legal representation. In some cases, this process can take a significant period of times and may still result in financial loss.<\/p>\n<p>Conversely, by working with a debt collection attorney such as ours, you can begin the legal proceedings immediately; an action that often allows the debtor to recognize the potentially serious consequences of ongoing delinquency, sometimes well before a civil judgment.<\/p>\n<h2>Compliance with Debtor and Creditor Rights<\/h2>\n<p>The agreement between a creditor and a debtor is one rift with complex laws that are designed to protect the rights of each party. Unfortunately, not all debt-collection efforts are executed in compliance with policies as outlined by the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, the Federal Trade Commission (FTC), or other governing bodies.<\/p>\n<p>For that reason, Chuckstern Murphy Law Firm also represent the debtors who have had their rights violated by a creditor or debt collection agency that has failed to follow the rules and regulations as they pertain to collections.<\/p>\n<p>Further, because we are well versed in debt collection law, we can work with creditors to ensure that they meet all legal requirements associated with debt collections. This includes the preparation and issuance of a Demand Letter.<\/p>\n<p>Regardless of what circumstances have led you to seek a debt collection attorney in  Fresno or Fresnno County, <a href=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/case-results\/\">we will help lead you<\/a>\u00a0through what can be a complex process, and help you receive the justice and financial resolution that you are legally entitled.<\/p>\n<h2>Receive Your Free Consultation<\/h2>\n<p>If you\u2019re considering taking legal action against a debtor or creditor, then we urge you to contact us today to begin the process. All potential new clients will receive a free initial case evaluation, at which point we can discuss your rights and potential paths towards resolution.<\/p>\n<p>Find out how we can help you by calling our  Fresno office at 415-217-9456 or our Fresno office at 415-217-9456. Or, sign up for a <a href=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/contact-us\/fresno-office\/\">free consultation online<\/a>\u00a0or contact us online at our <a href=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/contact-us\/fresno-office\/\"> Fresno<\/a>\u00a0or <a href=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/contact-us\/westlake-village-office\/\">Fresno<\/a>\u00a0offices.<\/p>\n<p>We look forward to hearing from you and hope to help you resolve your debt collection concerns.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row triangle_shape=&#8221;no&#8221;][vc_column][vc_empty_space][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]<\/p>\n<\/div>",
    "protected": false
  },
  "excerpt": {
    "rendered": "<p>[vc_row triangle_shape=&#8221;no&#8221;][vc_column][vc_column_text] The collection of a debt owed is a fundamental phase in any financial agreement, and failure to do so can have long-term fiscal implications. At Chuckstern Murphy Law Firm, we want to make sure your debt cases are handled quickly and efficiently. Whether you\u2019re an independent contractor seeking money owed or a multi-national organization attempting to collect an outstanding debt, we can help you collect the money owed to you. Our debt collection attorneys in  Fresno and Fresnno County are ready to help you reach the desired outcome \u2013 and through the most direct&#8230;<\/p>\n",
    "protected": false
  },
